Bromus inermis

   [3917.jpg]
    Authority   Leysser
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms   Bromopsis inermis
   Common names smooth brome, brome grass
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3917

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A rhizomatous, sod-forming, leafy bunchgrass with
   dark green leaves reaching a height of 0.5-1.2 m. USES Used as pasture
   and for hay. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. Some fields of bromegrass have
   persistent for 25-30 years. COMMON NAMES Brome, Bromegrass, Chess,
   Smooth brome grass, Austrian brome, Hungarian brome, Russian brome.
   FURTHER INF Brome is native of Europe and Asia. It often grows wild
   along roadsites, ditches, and in moist, woody areas and is very
   resistant to tramping, and wind and water erosion. It has certain
   winter requirements.

   Sources
